PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12122
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We examine an export game where two (home and foreign) firms produce vertically differentiated products. The foreign firm is more R otherwise, reciprocal dumping occurs. For some parameters, a domestic antidumping policy leads to a quality reversal in the international market whereby the home firm becomes the quality leader. This policy is desirable for the implementing country, though world welfare decreases.
ER  - 

